Now that you're here, Arithitar most certainly knows that you are here as well.

1061
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:13,000
Yeah, we've talked to like everyone on the way.

1062
00:48:13,000 --> 00:48:14,000
Yeah.

1063
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:25,000
If you were to attempt to make an escape, you may not be able to do so as long as he is able to fly and attack your ship.

1064
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:27,000
Oh, yeah.

1065
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:29,000
Well, we'll probably just have to kill him then.

1066
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:32,000
I anticipated you would be saying that.

1067
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:43,000
There are some things I can give you if you can help me escape and bring things with me.

1068
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:44,000
Sure.

1069
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:49,000
What I would like to bring are the stolen goods from the Arcane Brotherhood.

1070
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:51,000
Of course.

1071
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:53,000
My organization would wish to have those back.

1072
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:58,000
Most of those are located in the Scriptorium, which is located right next door.

1073
00:48:58,000 --> 00:49:00,000
She points to the back corner.

1074
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:02,000
Yeah, the toads.

1075
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,000
No, no.

1076
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:16,000
She points to the back and says here, which you can't see, but she points back here and says back through there is a large library of volumes of books.

1077
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:18,000
And she says the toads?

1078
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:20,000
Well, both the toads.

1079
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:29,000
The next two doors down on the left, back up that way, there's a room full of giant toads writing scripts.

1080
00:49:29,000 --> 00:49:37,000
They are keeping track of Arithatar's possessions, as well as they do keep very good history of the North.

1081
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:38,000
They do.

1082
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:40,000
They're quite intelligent creatures.

1083
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:45,000
Do you think that they'll have a history of what the deal was for him to give up the Dracorn?

1084
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:47,000
They may.

1085
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,000
I don't know.

1086
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:52,000
When we asked about the Dracorn, though, they didn't give us any information.

1087
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:57,000
If you ask them directly, then they didn't tell you they might not have that information.

1088
00:49:57,000 --> 00:50:00,000
What they keep is more valuable information.

1089
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:04,000
But that would keep a ledger of where it went, right, and how to get there.

1090
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:07,000
Perhaps only who it went to.

1091
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:09,000
That's a good start.

1092
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:18,000
She says, what I would like to bring, the majority of it is in the scriptorium, but some of it may be in Arithatar's lair as well.

1093
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:22,000
Well, we'll kill him first, and then you can take anything you want.

1094
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:29,000
She goes to her desk, or she's at her desk, she opens a drawer and pulls out a ring and lays it on the desk,

1095
00:50:29,000 --> 00:50:37,000
and then goes to a fold in the tapestries on the wall and pulls out two arrows and says,

1096
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:46,000
this is a ring of cold resistance, and these are two arrows of dragon slaying that I've been able to craft since I've been here.

1097
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:49,000
They may help you in your fight against Arithatar.

1098
00:50:49,000 --> 00:50:55,000
I can tell you how his lair is laid out.

1099
00:50:55,000 --> 00:51:00,000
I know Arithatar tends to use traps in his lairs.

1100
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:05,000
I cannot tell you where those are as he keeps a close eye on me when I go down there.

1101
00:51:05,000 --> 00:51:10,000
So just be wary when you are down there to watch out for traps.

1102
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:11,000
Yes.

1103
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:17,000
There are two entrances, one through the scriptorium, which is directly behind us here,

1104
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:25,000
another in a storeroom further down the hall, which drops into a further area from where he is located.

1105
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:30,000
She begins describing the whole just of his realm there.

1106
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:37,000
He is generally in the westmost area of his lair.

1107
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:45,000
Dropping down from the scriptorium, you will go into his perch area where he sometimes spends his time.

1108
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:46,000
Perching.

1109
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:49,000
Perching and lounging, if you will.

1110
00:51:49,000 --> 00:51:50,000
Okay, hold on.

1111
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:56,000
I'm imagining a big like one of those little like Tweety Bird has that swing.

1112
00:51:56,000 --> 00:51:58,000
Is it like that?

1113
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:03,000
Well, it's more of a shelf, but it is where he often will be sleeping.

1114
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:12,000
And then the abyss where he spends most of his time down from that drops down.

1115
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:14,000
He calls it the abyss.

1116
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:15,000
That's what I call it.

1117
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:16,000
It's cheery.

1118
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:19,000
Yes, it is a very cold.

1119
00:52:19,000 --> 00:52:22,000
You thought this whole iceberg was cold?

1120
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:25,000
It is colder down there.

1121
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:32,000
The second entrance, which is over in the storeroom there, drops down into an area with large ice pillars.

1122
00:52:32,000 --> 00:52:38,000
And then there are two tunnels which lead into the abyss.

1123
00:52:38,000 --> 00:52:39,000
Okay.

1124
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:41,000
Where do you guys think we should go down?

1125
00:52:41,000 --> 00:52:47,000
Well, I mean, at least the scriptorium we know just goes right there.

1126
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:49,000
Do we know where the storeroom is?

1127
00:52:49,000 --> 00:52:53,000
Because we could run into more creatures out, get into that storeroom.

1128
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:54,000
It's not too far, though.

1129
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:58,000
You haven't been to it yet, but the way she describes it, it is...

1130
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:00,000
Just down the hall and to the left.

1131
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:01,000
Oh, I see.

1132
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,000
Yeah.

1133
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:04,000
Because I think that would give us probably...

1134
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:08,000
I think I prefer not to be on a perch.

1135
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:11,000
Because how high up is that perch?

1136
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:20,000
That perch is 16 feet and then the abyss goes down to zero.

1137
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:26,000
So it's like a 16-foot drop from the light blue area to the dark blue area.

1138
00:53:26,000 --> 00:53:28,000
I think that's a survivable drop.

1139
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:32,000
I also feel like perch seems like maybe a bad idea in case he's sleeping there.

1140
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:33,000
Yeah, because although...

1141
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:34,000
Or maybe that's good.

1142
00:53:34,000 --> 00:53:36,000
Maybe we want to sneak up on him when he's sleeping.

1143
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:38,000
I prefer to kill him in his sleep.

1144
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:45,000
Do you guys happen to have the name of the previous ice dragon that we fought written down anywhere?

1145
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:47,000
Perhaps.

1146
00:53:47,000 --> 00:53:52,000
Because I'm thinking if we can go in there and say, we don't want to kill you,

1147
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:57,000
but we've done this before and we can reference the dragon that we killed,

1148
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:58,000
then that might be...

1149
00:53:58,000 --> 00:54:00,000
He might take our threat a little more seriously.

1150
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:01,000
Is it Verem?

1151
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:05,000
No, that's one of the head dragon cult people, isn't it?

1152
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,000
Yeah.

1153
00:54:06,000 --> 00:54:07,000
Glazhale.

1154
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:08,000
Glazhale.

1155
00:54:08,000 --> 00:54:09,000
That sounds right.

1156
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:13,000
I have white dragon's ice and stuff written beside it.

1157
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:14,000
Perfect.

1158
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:16,000
Perfect, yeah.

1159
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:17,000
Blagothkis?

1160
00:54:17,000 --> 00:54:18,000
No, who's that?

1161
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:20,000
Was that the ice giant?

1162
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:21,000
Blagothkis?

1163
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:22,000
Yeah.

1164
00:54:22,000 --> 00:54:24,000
Yes, he's a giant cloud giant.

1165
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:25,000
Okay.

1166
00:54:25,000 --> 00:54:26,000
Gleshale, then.

1167
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,000
How about Gleshale?

1168
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:29,000
I think it's with a Z though.

1169
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:31,000
I think it's Glazhale.

1170
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:32,000
Could be.

1171
00:54:32,000 --> 00:54:34,000
I always just have to try and do it phonetically.

1172
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:35,000
Yeah, it's a good call.

1173
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:36,000
So, yeah.

1174
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:40,000
Because I think if he's not sleeping and we can't just sneak out,

1175
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:45,000
I think we need to announce ourselves and lay like an ultimatum.

1176
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:46,000
Absolutely.

1177
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:47,000
Ultimatum.

1178
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:49,000
An ultimatum.

1179
00:54:49,000 --> 00:54:51,000
Just go in ultimatum.

1180
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:53,000
Put that devil fruit out of here.

1181
00:54:53,000 --> 00:54:56,000
I figure if we drop in there and can actually reference the fact

1182
00:54:56,000 --> 00:54:58,000
that we have killed an ice dragon before,

1183
00:54:58,000 --> 00:55:00,000
and we don't really want to kill this guy,

1184
00:55:00,000 --> 00:55:01,000
we just want to be on our way.

1185
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:02,000
Of course.

1186
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:03,000
Maybe he'll let us go.

1187
00:55:03,000 --> 00:55:04,000
Oh, yeah.

1188
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:09,000
But he needs to let us go and Macoth,

1189
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:11,000
which he just might not be willing to do.

1190
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:12,000
But who knows?

1191
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:14,000
We don't have to tell him that part.

1192
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:17,000
How are we going to sneak her and what she wants to bring out?

1193
00:55:17,000 --> 00:55:18,000
That is a good question.

1194
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:21,000
Because she is not coming with us right now, right?

1195
00:55:21,000 --> 00:55:24,000
No, I have a feeling she'll probably stay in her fort.

1196
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:26,000
She won't come with you down to the lair?

1197
00:55:26,000 --> 00:55:27,000
Is that what you're asking?

1198
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:28,000
Yeah.

1199
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:29,000
Yes.

1200
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:30,000
No, no.

1201
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:35,000
She describes the entrance to the lair to you,

1202
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:38,000
and it is from the scriptorium,

1203
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:43,000
it is relatively easy to get down,

1204
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:47,000
but neither area is easy to get out of.

1205
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:52,000
Arithatar wishes prisoners and guests alike,

1206
00:55:52,000 --> 00:55:55,000
he makes sure that it's not easy for them to get out of.

1207
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:56,000
Okay.

1208
00:55:56,000 --> 00:55:59,000
So when we go down, we leave a rope dangling.

1209
00:55:59,000 --> 00:56:01,000
Well, Flint has that ladder.

1210
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:02,000
I do have my ladder.

1211
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:03,000
True.

1212
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:06,000
And I also have, how big are these openings?

1213
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:07,000
20 feet.

1214
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:14,000
Whereas area 11 is closer to about 10 to 15 feet across.

1215
00:56:14,000 --> 00:56:22,000
She says that he is able to clamber up and down this passage without difficulty.

1216
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:23,000
Both of them.

1217
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:25,000
Because I also have guacamole.

1218
00:56:25,000 --> 00:56:31,000
And the chute goes down about 60 feet to the roof of area 19,

1219
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:35,000
after which there is a 15-foot drop to the ice platform.

1220
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:38,000
Ah, this is going to be fun.

1221
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:40,000
It's like a little, it's like an ice slide.

1222
00:56:40,000 --> 00:56:42,000
It was like we're doing, we're louging.

1223
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:43,000
Yes.

1224
00:56:43,000 --> 00:56:45,000
We're skeletoning down there, right?

1225
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:47,000
Exactly.

1226
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:50,000
And guacamole could probably help us get out.

1227
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:51,000
Right.

1228
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:57,000
If we needed to, at least through the bigger one, probably the number six.

1229
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:58,000
Six.

1230
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:03,000
Probably not fly out, but she's got these giant talons and can probably,

1231
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:08,000
if a dragon can crawl its way out of there, I'm assuming an owl could do the same.

1232
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:10,000
Sounds reasonable to me.

1233
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:14,000
Yeah, the chute and the other one is a 60-foot drop as well.

1234
00:57:14,000 --> 00:57:16,000
A 60-foot drop or a 60-foot slide?

1235
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:18,000
A 60-foot drop.

1236
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,000
That sounds lovely.

1237
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:22,000
60 feet to the top of a platform.

1238
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:27,000
Okay, so I say we go down the one in the scriptorium

1239
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:31,000
because that's a slide and a 15-foot drop, correct?

1240
00:57:31,000 --> 00:57:37,000
Yeah, you could make it down there with ropes or some other climbing gear.

1241
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:41,000
Okay, but 60-foot drop just seems like...

1242
00:57:41,000 --> 00:57:42,000
Sounds like it's going to hurt.

1243
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:45,000
Make a saving throw to see if you plunge to your death.

1244
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:46,000
Yes.

1245
00:57:46,000 --> 00:57:49,000
Yeah, so, all right, let's go down there.

1246
00:57:49,000 --> 00:57:52,000
Can we have a long rest there in that nice warm tent

1247
00:57:52,000 --> 00:57:55,000
and get all our hit points back before we fight the dragon?

1248
00:57:55,000 --> 00:57:56,000
She says,

1249
00:57:56,000 --> 00:58:00,000
You may help me get what I need ready in the scriptorium

1250
00:58:00,000 --> 00:58:03,000
before we, hopefully, depart.

1251
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:07,000
You may rest until you feel ready to fight Aruthator.

1252
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:11,000
As long as he is down there and you are up here, I feel you will be safe.

1253
00:58:11,000 --> 00:58:13,000
She parts the fabric of her tent

1254
00:58:13,000 --> 00:58:18,000
and leads you back into the scriptorium where there are walls covered

1255
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:23,000
and bookshelves covered with scrolls and books and writings.

1256
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:27,000
And she tosses you a bag, a rather small one by the looks of it,

1257
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:30,000
and says, start filling her up.

